22/04/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Romanian police officers assigned to EULEX have been caught smuggling cigarettes and alcohol out of Kosovo, local media reported on Wednesday (April 21st). Sixteen Romanian officers were travelling by a bus that was stopped late Tuesday at the Blace border crossing. Macedonian customs authorities say the goods -- 341 cartons of cigarettes and 133 litres of alcohol -- were hidden in the bus used by the EULEX mission. Reportedly, the cigarettes belonged to the driver, and the alcohol belonged to passengers. The head of mission has asked for an immediate investigation. (Koha Ditore, Zeri - 22/04/10; RTK, Kohavision, Klan Kosova - 21/04/10)
